THE Hawks in Northern Cape arrested a suspect (28) for business robbery on Monday, 4 July. According to Captain Tebogo Thebe, it was alleged that two suspects entered a post office in Vergenoeg in Mankurwane. “They pointed employees with a firearm and stole about R230 000. Community members followed them and managed to arrest one at a nearby house,” Thebe said. He was found with R110 000 in his possession and is expected to appear in the Galeshewe Magistrates Court soon.